#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:17
msgid ""
"Last week, part of the Kdenlive core team met in Amsterdam for a short "
"sprint, the highlight of which was a visit to the Blender Foundation."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:19
msgid ""
"Francesco Siddi, COO at Blender, provided us with a rare insight into "
"Blender’s history and precious advice about product management for Kdenlive "
"– we hope to implement some of these advices soon."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:21
msgid ""
"As the meeting took place on a Friday afternoon, we also had the opportunity"
" to attend their “Weekly”, which is an open session where artists and "
"developers share their progress of the past week on various Blender related "
"projects."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:23
msgid ""
"So thanks again to Francesco and everyone at the Blender Foundation for "
"their hospitality."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:25
msgid "On the next day, we discussed a few topics, including:"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:27
msgid "Refining the [audio workflow task][1]"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:28
msgid ""
"Proof of concept on how we can [improve clip timecode][2] – define a start "
"timecode when rendering"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:29
msgid ""
"Finalized an [MLT patch][3] to make rendering work without a display server "
"(required to make Flatpak pass our render test suite)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/amsterdam-sprint-report/index.md:30
msgid "Scratched [a][4] [few][5] [itches][6]"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:0
msgid "Kdenlive in Berlin"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:0
#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:0
#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:0
msgid "kdenlive"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:13
msgid "![](berlin-1.jpg \"Kdenlive team working\")"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:15
msgid ""
"From the 3rd to the 5th of September, the Kdenlive team was reunited in "
"Berlin for a sprint and to attend [Akademy][1], KDE's annual conference. "
"This was an occasion for us to meet in person since our team is spread "
"across continents, and to join our forces to make Kdenlive better. And I "
"must say this was one of the most productive sprints in Kdenlive's history!"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:17
msgid ""
"We were kindly hosted by [c-base][2] for our Sprint so a big thanks to the "
"team for welcoming us there!"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:19
msgid "Let's get into the details of what we did:"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:21
msgid ""
"We started by reviewing and updating our [roadmap][3], so it is easier to "
"understand what we are working on, what we plan and when. Another important "
"step towards improving our workflows is that we created issues for each of "
"these goals where the details will be discussed, so everyone can follow and "
"possibly help us on the road to success."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:23
msgid "Dopesheet"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:24
msgid ""
"Very exciting, I received a grant from the [NGI Zero Commons Fund][4] "
"through [NLnet][5] to work on a dopesheet feature in Kdenlive. This will "
"bring a much improved keyframing interface with powerful features. We "
"discussed what core features we want in it and some drafts on how that would"
" work. This feature won't be ready for the December release, but I will post"
" updates on the progress of this task in the coming months."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:26
msgid ""
"We then reviewed specific parts of the UI that we would like to improve. All"
" these ideas will be discussed in specific issues so that we can refine the "
"implementation."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:28
msgid "Menu reorganization"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:29
msgid ""
"This task started two years ago but we never took time to finalize it. We "
"progressed a lot on this and you can expect it to land in the December "
"release. Among the changes, we decided to rename the `Project Bin` to "
"`Media`, `Render` to `Export`, and reorganize the menus to make things more "
"logical. We will make another blog to present these changes in detail once "
"this is done."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:31
msgid "Timeline toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:32
msgid ""
"We want to cleanup the UI, make the timeline timecode display cleaner and "
"get rid of the large *Master* button currently taking a lot of space."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:34
msgid "Monitor UI"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:35
msgid ""
"We plan to move the audio vu-meter to a collapsible vertical widget on the "
"right side of the monitor to free some space in the toolbar, make the zone "
"duration always visible and move the insert/overwrite actions currently in "
"the timeline toolbar there."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:37
msgid "Audio monitor"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:38
msgid ""
"When selecting an audio clip, the Clip Monitor currently displays a huge "
"audio waveform that is not that useful. We reviewed the UI to also display "
"an overview at the top, making it easier to zoom and see where you are in "
"the clip."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:42
msgid "Layout and docks"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:43
msgid ""
"We have several open issues regarding docking. One of the frequent request "
"we have is to save the layout per project file, since sometimes you want "
"very specific layouts for a project. We discussed how to make it happen and "
"are also evaluating switching the library managing the widgets docking to "
"[KDDockWidgets][6] that would bring us some very nice improvements like "
"being able to detach the timeline or group several undocked widgets together"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:45
msgid "![](team-berlin.jpg \"Kdenlive team working\")"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:46
msgid "Titler"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:47
msgid ""
"Our current titler does the job for simple tasks but many users would like "
"to be able to use some animation presets to make their titles more dynamic. "
"We discussed the possible options to make this a reality. Among the ideas, "
"we could use Lottie animations, since our video backend MLT already has "
"support to play them through the Glaxnimate module. Another option would be "
"to implement a Qml producer for MLT, allowing to play Qml files directly as "
"a video. Any help on that topic is welcome."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:49
msgid "Website"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:50
msgid ""
"We have some planned changes to make our website look better and discussed "
"some of the options."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:52
msgid "And all the rest"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:53
msgid ""
"![](team-restaurant.jpg \"Kdenlive team in a nice restaurant\") We discussed"
" tons of other things and even managed to shoot some interviews of our team "
"members. Less relevant maybe for users but we also reviewed some of the "
"administrative and trademark issues, and CI/CD issues"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:56
msgid "Akademy 2025"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:57
msgid ""
"Akademy was also an occasion to have interesting exchanges, notably with "
"Glaxnimate's maintainer, Plasma developers and more. We are now back home "
"with tons of ideas and TODO's, and the next release of Kdenlive, to be "
"launched in December, will shine with some of the improvements we prepared "
"during this week in Berlin !"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/berlin-sprint/index.md:59
msgid ""
"If you would like to help our small team, you are always welcome to "
"contribute by giving some feedback, talk about us, create a merge request or"
" donate."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/fundraising-final-report/index.md:0
msgid "Kdenlive fundraising final report"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/fundraising-final-report/index.md:0
#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:0
#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:0
msgid "Fundraising"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/fundraising-final-report/index.md:14
msgid ""
"From 6th to 10th of September 2024, part of the [Kdenlive Team was in "
"Germany][1] to attend the annual KDE convention [Akademy][2] and used that "
"opportunity of being together at the same location to have a sprint. It was "
"good to meet face to face and to sit down and tackle some issues together. "
"One of the topic discussed was improving our communication towards users, so"
" here is a much needed update on the status of our fundraiser! This post "
"should have been published a few months earlier but there were so much "
"things happening around Kdenlive that it was hard to follow, so sorry for "
"the delay!"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/fundraising-final-report/index.md:16
msgid ""
"It’s been a bit more than 2 years since we launched our very successful "
"fundraiser. This allowed us to fund some much wanted features, and as a side"
" goal, allowed me to spend more time on Kdenlive. Thanks to your donations, "
"I will be able to dedicate two days per week to Kdenlive instead of one. "
"Note that this only sponsors part of my work as I spend much more time to "
"Kdenlive, but hopefully this will relieve some stress and I will have a "
"healthier weekly rhythm."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/fundraising-final-report/index.md:18
msgid ""
"During this time, there were around 1,900 commits to the Kdenlive "
"repository, meaning about 3.8 commits per day! We didn’t take that much "
"vacation, did we? Also worth noting is that we handled the port to Qt6 "
"during that time, which was a big task and took a lot of effort."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2025/fundraising-final-report/index.md:20
msgid ""
"So now for the status of the fundraiser, here is what has been done so far "
"and what is left. All major things were implemented in the 24.12 release so "
"that we can move on to our next goals soon."
msgstr ""

