#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:0
msgid "Parametrized Keyframes - Status Report, February 2026"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:12
msgid ""
"In the last month, I have mostly been working on refactoring the Kdenlive "
"keyframes system to make it more powerful. This is part of a [NGI Zero "
"Commons grant via NLnet][1]."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:14
msgid "Improving existing parameters handling"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:15
msgid ""
"A first step in preparation for this work was to improve the usability of "
"some effects. In Kdenlive, we support several effect libraries, like MLT, "
"Frei0r and FFmpeg's avfilters. Not all effects expose their parameters in "
"the same way. For example in MLT, we have a rectangle parameter allowing to "
"define a zone in a video frame. Other effects expose several independent "
"parameters for a rectangle, namely x, y, width and height."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:17
msgid ""
"Currently, these effects are displayed with a list of sliders for each "
"value: ![](fillborders-before.png \"Effect parameters before the change\")"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:20
msgid ""
"With my latest changes, these will be handled like a rectangle, which means "
"it can directly be manipulated in the monitor overlay. ![](fillborders-"
"after.png \"Effect parameters now\")"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:23
msgid ""
"Another improvement is the addition of Point parameters which will allow "
"selecting a point in the monitor."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:25
msgid "These changes are planned to be in the 26.04 release."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:27
msgid "Boosting keyframes"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:28
msgid ""
"The next improvement being worked on is support of keyframes per parameter. "
"Currently, once you add a keyframe to an effect, it is applied to all "
"parameters, which is sometimes not wanted. This will also allow animating "
"only one parameter while leaving the others parameters fixed. Below is a "
"screenshot of a basic UI created to test the feature. ![](dopesheet.png "
"\"parameter independant keyframes\") Also, currently you cannot see "
"keyframes for different effects at the same time. Regrouping keyframes for "
"all effects in one place will enable more powerful editing."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:33
msgid "Kdenlive needs your support"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/dopesheet-status-1-26/index.md:34
msgid ""
"Our small team has been working for years to build an intuitive open source "
"video editor that does not track you, does not use your data, and respects "
"your privacy. However, to ensure a proper development requires resources, so"
" please consider a [donation][3] if you enjoy using Kdenlive - even small "
"amounts can make a big difference."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:0
msgid "State of Kdenlive - 2026"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:15
msgid ""
"In 2025, the Kdenlive team continued grinding to push the project forward "
"through steady development, collaboration, and community support. Over the "
"past year we’ve found a nice balance between adding new features, bug "
"fixing, polishing the user interface, and improving performance and "
"workflow, with stability taking priority over feature creep."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:17
msgid ""
"We relaunched the website with a new content management system, refreshed "
"some content and the design, and restored historic content dating back to "
"2002. We also strengthened upstream collaboration with the MLT developers "
"and contributed several improvements to OpenTimelineIO."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:19
msgid "Here’s a look at what we've been up to and what is ahead."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:21
msgid "RELEASE HIGHLIGHTS"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:23
msgid ""
"As part of [KDE Apps][1], we follow the KDE Gear [release cycle][2], with "
"three major releases each year—in April, August, and December—each followed "
"by three point maintenance releases."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:25
msgid "25.04.0"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:27
msgid ""
"This release added a powerful automatic masking tool and brought the last "
"batch of features from our last fundraiser."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:29
msgid "[-> _Read full changelog_][3]"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:35
msgid ""
"{{< video src-webm=background-removal.webm autoplay=\"true\" muted=\"true\" "
"loop=\"true\" controls=\"false\" ratio=\"0.67\">}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:37
msgid ""
"The new Object Segmentation plugin based on the [SAM2][4] model allows to "
"remove any selected object from the background. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:40
msgid "{{< card title=\"OpenTimelineIO\" >}} ![otio](otiov.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:43
msgid ""
"We rewrote our OpenTimelineIO import and export function using the C++ "
"library. Now you can exchange projects with other editing applications that "
"support this open source file format. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:46
msgid "{{< card title=\"Waveform improvements\" >}} ![waveforns](waves.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:49
msgid ""
"Audio waveform generation got a 300% performance boost, along with a "
"refactored sampling method that accurately renders the audio signal and "
"higher-resolution waveforms for greater precision. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:55
msgid "25.08.0"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:57
msgid ""
"This release focused heavily on stabilization, bringing over 300 commits and"
" fixing more than 15 crashes. Instead of major new features, the effort went"
" into polishing and bug fixing."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:59
msgid "[-> _Read full changelog_][5]"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:63
msgid "{{< card title=\"Audio Mixer\" >}} ![mixer](mixer.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:66
msgid ""
"We redesigned the audio mixer bringing levels with clearer visuals and "
"thresholds. We also did some code refactoring and cleanup. This change fixes"
" issues with HiDPI displays with fractional scaling. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:69
msgid ""
"{{< card title=\"Markers and Guides\" >}} {{< video src=markers-guides.mp4 "
"autoplay=\"true\" muted=\"true\" loop=\"true\" controls=\"false\" "
"ratio=\"0.6\">}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:72
msgid ""
"Guides and Markers got a major overhaul this release to improve the project "
"organization. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:75
msgid ""
"{{< card title=\"Titler improvements\" >}} {{< video src=titler.mp4 "
"autoplay=\"true\" muted=\"true\" loop=\"true\" controls=\"false\" "
"ratio=\"0.55\">}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:78
msgid ""
"This release the titler received some much needed love like improved SVG and"
" image support with ability to move and resize items, added center resize "
"with Shift + Drag, and renamed the Pattern tab to Templates and moved the "
"templates dropdown to it {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:83
msgid "25.12.0"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:85
msgid ""
"The focus of this release cycle was on improving the user experience and "
"polishing the user interface."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:87
msgid "[-> _Read full changelog_][6]"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:91
msgid "{{< card title=\"Welcome Screen\" >}} ![welcome_screen](welcome.webp)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:94
msgid ""
"We added a new first-run launch screen for first time users as well as added"
" a Welcome Screen allowing to easily launch recent projects. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:97
msgid ""
"{{< card title=\"Docking System\" >}} {{< video src-webm=docking.webm "
"autoplay=\"true\" muted=\"true\" loop=\"true\" controls=\"false\" "
"ratio=\"0.6\">}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:100
msgid ""
"We added a new, more flexible docking system that lets you group widgets, "
"show or hide them on demand, and save layouts as separate files that can be "
"shared or stored within projects. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:103
msgid ""
"{{< card title=\"Redesigned monitor\" >}} {{< video src-webm=audio-"
"monitor.webm autoplay=\"true\" muted=\"true\" loop=\"true\" "
"controls=\"false\" ratio=\"0.6\">}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:106
msgid ""
"The audio waveform in the Project Monitor got a revamped interface with an "
"added minimap. {{< /card >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:111
msgid "THE ROAD AHEAD"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:113
msgid "26.04"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:115
msgid ""
"This next release is just around the corner and brings a nice batch of nifty"
" new features like monitor mirroring and animated transition previews, "
"making it much easier to visualize how they will look before applying them. "
"Additionally, dropping a transition onto the timeline can now automatically "
"adjust its duration to match the clips above and below, saving time and "
"reducing manual tweaking."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:117
msgid ""
"This feature allows you to mirror any monitor while working in fullscreen "
"mode. It’s especially useful when working with multiple displays or "
"collaborating with others in the editing room."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:119
msgid ""
"{{< video src-webm=anim-prev.webm autoplay=\"true\" muted=\"true\" "
"loop=\"true\" controls=\"false\" ratio=\"0.75\">}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:121
msgid "OTHER NOTEWORTHY FEATURES"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:123
msgid "Change the playback speed of multiple clips at once"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:124
msgid ""
"Import a clip directly from the timeline context menu and insert it at the "
"click position"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:125
msgid ""
"Option to always zoom toward the mouse position instead of the timeline "
"playhead"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:126
msgid "Generate audio thumbnails for sequences"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:128
msgid "ROADMAP"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:130
msgid ""
"Our [roadmap][7] is constantly being reviewed and updated, and some of the "
"upcoming highlights include implementing the new features in MLT, the "
"multimedia framework which powers Kdenlive. Some exciting upcoming features "
"include 10/12 bit color support, [playback optimizations (decoding)][8], and"
" [OpenFX][9] support. _(Shoutout to a Kdenlive community member for leading "
"this effort)_. Also expected is a refactoring of the subtitle system as well"
" as continuing to develop the _Advanced Trimming Tools_."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:132
msgid "DOPESHEET"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:134
msgid ""
"We are currently working on refactoring the keyframing system and "
"implementing a Dopesheet, basically it is a dedicated timeline for managing "
"and viewing keyframes from multiple effects simultaneously. This work will "
"also introduce per-parameter keyframing (currently, once you add a keyframe "
"to an effect, it is applied to all parameters by default). More info can be "
"found in the last [status report][10]. This work is made possible through an"
" [NGI Zero Commons grant via NLnet][11]."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:136
msgid "![dopesheet](dopesheet.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:138
msgid "MICROSOFT STORE"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:140
msgid ""
"We have been working on [enabling and fixing][12] multiple modules in MLT to"
" compile with MSVC allowing us to ship Kdenlive in the Microsoft Store soon."
" Another advantage is that it will allow to run unit tests on our [CI for "
"Windows.][13]"
msgstr ""

