#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:196
msgid "AMSTERDAM SPRINT"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:198
msgid "![Amsterdam sprint](kdenlive-blender.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:200
msgid ""
"In February, part of the Kdenlive core team met in [Amsterdam for a short "
"sprint][14], highlighted by a visit to the Blender Foundation, where we met "
"with Francesco Siddi and he shared valuable insights into Blender’s history "
"and offered advice on product management for Kdenlive. We also attended "
"their weekly open session, where artists and developers present progress on "
"ongoing projects. During the sprint, we discussed and advanced several "
"technical topics, some highlights include:"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:202
msgid "Refining the audio workflow task"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:203
msgid "Developing a proof of concept to improve clip timecode handling"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:204
msgid ""
"Finishing an MLT Framework patch to enable rendering without a display "
"server (needed for Flatpak testing)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:206
msgid "BERLIN SPRINT"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:208
msgid "![Kdenlive Berlin](kdenlive-berlin.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:210
msgid ""
"The [Berlin sprint][15] was one of our most productive gatherings to date. "
"Most of the team was there in person, and we also connected online with "
"those who couldn’t make it. We discussed just about every aspect of the "
"project, from roadmap planning to upcoming features and workflow "
"improvements. Some of the highlights include:"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:212
msgid ""
"Evaluated the current state of the Titler and discussed possible integration"
" with Glaxnimate"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:213
msgid "Reorganized the Menu structure"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:214
msgid "Developed a proof of concept for using KDDockWidgets"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:215
msgid ""
"Redesigned and started development of the audio clip view in the Clip "
"Monitor"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:217
msgid "Thanks to the nice folks at [c-base][16] who kindly hosted us."
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:219
msgid "AKADEMY 2025"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:221
msgid "![Akademy](akademy.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#: content/news/2026/state-2026/index.md:223
msgid ""
"Akademy is always a great opportunity to exchange ideas with the broader KDE"
" and Qt communities. One of the highlights was meeting the maintainer of "
"Glaxnimate, where we discussed common goals and ways to collaborate. This "
"year, [Akademy will be in Graz][17] on the 19-24 of September, and we hope "
"to see you there."
msgstr ""

